Fix duplicate command block in backtesting page (Task #11)

Three targeted changes to static/js/pages/backtesting.js:

1. Removed #bt-cmd div from #bt-status-card HTML template — the old
   post-run command block inside the status card is gone. Only one
   command element exists: #bt-cmd-preview in the Configuration card.

2. Removed cmdEl variable and _renderCommandBlock(cmdEl, data.meta.command)
   call from _updateStatus() — eliminates the stale reference and prevents
   any attempt to render into the now-deleted #bt-cmd element.

3. Guarded _refreshCommandPreview() against empty-pair state — if no pairs
   are selected, the container is cleared (innerHTML = '') instead of
   rendering a bare "COMMAND / Copy" shell with no tokens. The preview
   only renders when at least one pair is checked.

4. Added _refreshCommandPreview() call after successful patchConfig() in
   _wireConfigSyncEvents() — the live command now updates immediately when
   strategy, wallet, max-trades, or stake-amount fields are changed and
   saved to config.json.

Bug fix: _getSelectedPairs() was called without its required listId
argument — corrected to pass 'bt-pairs-list' (matching every other call
site in the file).

No changes to hyperopt.js, CSS, or backend files.
